Muzikayise Malephane appeared in court and was charged with the murder of Tshegofatso Pule on Wednesday. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A 31-year-old suspect has appeared in the Roodepoort magistrate's court in connection with the murder of Tshegofatso Pule. The case has been postponed. READ: Suspect arrested for Tshegofatso Pule's murder Pule's body was found in a veld in Durban Deep, Roodepoort earlier this month. Prosecutors have said they could add on charges to the charge of premeditated murder. READ: Femicide in the spotlight South Africa The case has been postponed to 24 June where the suspect will apply to obtain legal representation. He will remain in police custody until the next court date. Pule's death is one of several murders of women in the country recently and has lead to calls for the government to do more about South Africa's femicide crisis.